description: Well maintained 3 bedroom home in the walking community of Bellevue. Wiring has been updated, electrician removed old knob and tube! Interior freshly painted. Covered front porch perfect for relaxing outside. Entry w/coat closet then leads into spacious living room. Charming living area w/an almost 6 ft fireplace & mantle w/window on both sides & large front window. Nicely sized dining room is light & bright - large back windows & it is partially open to kitchen. In the kitchen there is add'l drop zone counter & cabinets near backdoor to deck & yard. Take the stairs to 2nd floor you will see the Craftsman style woodwork, gorgeous wood doors w/glass knobs & more hardwood flooring upstairs, Primary bedroom w/10 x 5 walk in closet, 2 more bedrooms & full bath. Back to lower level: main basement w/furnace (21x10), laundry/utility room (14x10), 19x 11 area that could be finished, workshop w/built-ins (7x6) & storage (9x7).  Just a few minute walk to shopping, restaurants & Schools.

description: Move in ready 4 square charmer with loads of renovations and character still intact. Minutes form Bellevue's business district and an easy commute to the city, 589 Forest offers an updated open concept kitchen/dining room layout with sliding doors to a wonderful back deck and lower level patio. Hardwoods and preserved built in mantle and cabinetry preserve the details of a century old house, while the updated mechanicals, appliances, carpet and paint throughout make this a home you can call home from day one. Upstairs offers 3 bedrooms, one with its own ensuite bath, as well as another full bath for the house. The third floor is one giant flex space, with ample room and storage for another bedroom, play room, guest rooms or home offices.
